    • Page
      IAS and PDP1 Instruction Set Equivalence Page

      IAS and PDP1 Instruction Equivalence
      IAS INSTRUCTIONS PDP1 EQUIVALENT FUNCTION
      LOAD LAC Load the Accumulator from Memory
      STOR DAC Save/Deposit the Accumulator to Memory
      ADD ADD Add Accumulator
      SUB SUB Subtract Accumulator
      MUL MUL Multiply Accumulator
      DIV DIV Divide Accumulator
      JUMP JMP Unconditional Branching
      JUMP + SZA Skip if Zero Accumulator
        SPA Skip if Positive Accumulator  (Including 0)
        SMA Skip if Minus Accumulator

    • Quiz
      Assembly Language Programming Exercise (Graded) Quiz

      Convert the IAS Program to convert Fahrenheit to Centigrade and determine whether  the temperature is feverish or not (USING DWORDS)

      0 JUMP(10,0:19)
      1 132 Initial Value
      2 32 Constant
      3 5 Constant
      4 9 Constant
      5 TEMP Result
      6 1 With Fever
      7 0 Without Fever
      8 38 Temp Cut OFF
      9 Decision
      10L LOAD M(1) AC=132
      10R SUB M(2) AC=AC-32
      11L MUL M(3) AC=AC*5
      11R DIV M(4) AC=AC/9
      12L STORE M(5) M(5)=AC
      12R LOAD M(6)
      13L STOR M(9)
      13R LOAD M(5)
      14L SUB M(8)
      14R JUMP+ (16,0:19)
      15L LOAD M(7)
      15R STOR M(9)
      16L JUMP (16,0:19)

    • Assignment
      ASSIGNMENT - 5 bit to Decimal Decoder Using 2 7 -Segment Displays in Circuitverse (GRADED)

      Using Circuitverse create a 5 bit to Decimal Decoder using 2 7segment Display as output.

      1. Input the 5 bit Decoder Truth Table into Combinational Analysis Tool  of circuitverse.

      2. Generate the corresponding circuit.

      3.  Create another circuit and Insert the 5 bit Decoder as a Subcircuit.

      4.  Connect the Subcircuit to Inputs and Outputs to the 2 7 segment displays

    • Assignment
      Boolean Logic Project (deadline: Nov 15, 2024) Assignment

      Create a Fixed Point Calculator (Addition and Subtraction Only) circuit in circuit verse that accepts inputs in 

      Single Digit Hexadecimal and computes the sum or difference between 2 whole number inputs A and B.

       

      The circuit should contain a Hex keyboard and Encoder that accepts user input in Hexadecimal.


      It should use a 4bit ALU from  circuitverse such that using the following control signals, the desired operation is done:

       

                      C2C1C0 =010   Perform Addition

                      C2C1C0 = 110  Perform Subtraction

       

      Furthermore, It should display results in Decimal using 2 7 segment displays.

       

      An additional component for converting negative results to positive with a negative sign indicated in an extra 7 segment display.

       

      The project rubrics are as follows:

      Hex Keyboard and Encoder

      30

      4 ALU with Adder and Subtracter

      20

      2 or 3 Digit Decimal Display with Decoder

      30

      2's Complement Converter

      20

      Total

      100

      Zip your circuitverse file and pass it using your familyname and firstname as the filename.

    • Assignment
      Simple Payroll Assignment

      Write a Javascript Program to Add,Delete employees in a payroll list.

      1. The payroll program should input the following:

      Employee Name         Days Worked          Daily Rate      Deduction Amount

      2. During Addition, the program should display the following in a table:

      No.    Employee Name      Days Worked      Daily Rate      Gross Pay     Deduction Amount    Net Pay

      where:

                No. = is the Payroll List Line number

                Gross Pay = Days Worked * Daily Rate

                 Net Pay = Gross Pay - Deduction Amount

       3. During Deletion, the program should ask for the Line Number to delete and update the table
